The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to detect mitotic figures in breast cancer tissue sections. This involves image analysis, registration, and data augmentation strategies to create stain invariant mitosis detectors. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as CNNs, knowledge distillation, and network ensembling, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with the computational requirements needed to process gigapixel whole-slide images (WSIs), which makes cs.DL (Deep Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the system in an independent multicenter cohort, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
